COVID19 Update(Nigeria): 
confirmed 0, deaths 0, recovered 0 Nigeria has recorded 91 new cases of COVID-19, taking the total to 873. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), confirmed this Wednesday night. Of the new cases, 74 are in Lagos,  5 in Katsina, 4 in Ogun, 2 in Delta, 2 in Edo, and1 in FCT, Kwara, Oyo and Adamawa state. As at 11:25 pm 22nd April there are 873 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported in Nigeria, the agency said. A total of 197 have been discharged with 28 deaths, NCDC said.  Source: Business Day Check your inbox or spam folder to confirm your subscription.  COVID19 Update(Nigeria):   By David Royal The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), on Wednesday, reported the nation has confirmed 91 new cases of coronavirus (COVID-19), a pandemic outbreak in the country. This brings the total number of cases confirmed to 873. According to NCDC, 74 cases were discovered in… April 22, 2020 In "News" COVID19 Update(Nigeria): Nigeria has confirmed additional 20 new cases of Coronavirus (Covid-19) making a total of 343 cases as at 09:50 pm 13th April. The NCDC said in its tweeter handle that there are 343 confirmed cases, 91 discharged, 10 deaths. A breakdown of cases shows Lagos- 189, FCT- 56,… April 13, 2020 In "News" Nigeria  added five new cases of Coronavirus late Saturday, bringing the total number to 214. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) confirmed this on its official Twitter handle on Saturday night Of the new cases, 3 are in Bauchi and 2 in the FCT. The country has also confirmed… April 4, 2020 In "News"